itemLabel: John St Aubyn, 1st Baron St Levan

wikipedia_page.main: John St Aubyn, 1st Baron St Levan  (23 October 1829 – 14 May 1908), known as Sir John St Aubyn, 2nd Baronet, from 1872 to 1887, was a British Liberal, and later Liberal Unionist, politician who sat in the House of Commons from 1858 until 1887 when he was raised to the peerage.
